1
00:00:57,390 --> 00:01:01,061
THE WONDERFOOLS

2
00:01:14,282 --> 00:01:16,576
THE HOLY BIBLE

3
00:01:41,101 --> 00:01:42,602
Are you managing okay in here?

4
00:01:43,353 --> 00:01:46,981
I've been having a good time,
thanks to you.

5
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:51,027
I hear you carry a Bible everywhere.

6
00:01:51,111 --> 00:01:53,571
So, have you been saved?

7
00:01:55,198 --> 00:01:56,783
At their core,

8
00:01:56,866 --> 00:02:00,495
all religions are mere deceptions
devised to control humans' anxiety.

9
00:02:00,995 --> 00:02:03,748
Fictitious and hypocritical words

10
00:02:03,832 --> 00:02:05,959
used to sugarcoat and glorify death.

11
00:02:07,877 --> 00:02:10,255
They're nothing but lies to incite people.

12
00:02:11,798 --> 00:02:12,966
However…

13
00:02:16,594 --> 00:02:18,179
I am the real deal.

14
00:02:20,431 --> 00:02:22,851
I really did create that child.

15
00:02:25,770 --> 00:02:26,855
That child.

16
00:02:27,522 --> 00:02:28,648
Where are they now?

17
00:02:30,650 --> 00:02:32,110
What do you mean by that?

18
00:02:33,069 --> 00:02:36,406
If the Child of Eternity truly does exist,

19
00:02:36,489 --> 00:02:37,866
prove it to me.

20
00:02:41,578 --> 00:02:43,621
This will be the last chance I give you

21
00:02:44,122 --> 00:02:46,749
to get out on parole.

22
00:02:48,459 --> 00:02:49,627
"Now faith

23
00:02:50,503 --> 00:02:52,964
is confidence in what we hope for

24
00:02:53,715 --> 00:02:55,884
and assurance about what we do not see."

25
00:03:00,013 --> 00:03:02,056
"All who believe in me

26
00:03:02,140 --> 00:03:03,975
shall receive salvation."

27
00:03:11,816 --> 00:03:12,650
But

28
00:03:14,485 --> 00:03:18,114
the Child of Eternity I remember
was definitely a boy.

29
00:03:19,532 --> 00:03:20,700
It's okay.

30
00:03:21,326 --> 00:03:22,869
I can't die.

31
00:03:23,745 --> 00:03:26,080
There's only one way to confirm it.

32
00:03:57,737 --> 00:04:00,114
Where'd she go?
Am I the only one who can't see her?

33
00:04:00,198 --> 00:04:02,492
Where did she go all of a sudden?

34
00:04:03,076 --> 00:04:04,035
Incredible.

35
00:04:47,203 --> 00:04:48,246
Chae…

36
00:05:32,999 --> 00:05:37,086
EPISODE 3
BRUTES AND BAD LUCK DO COME IN DROVES

37
00:05:37,170 --> 00:05:38,338
It was him,

38
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:39,672
Number 3972.

39
00:05:40,715 --> 00:05:42,592
Really? Are you sure it was 3972?

40
00:05:43,676 --> 00:05:44,510
Do you know him?

41
00:05:44,594 --> 00:05:47,096
He's the kid Pal-ho used to hate.
Remember?

42
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:49,724
When his ability first manifested,

43
00:05:49,807 --> 00:05:51,768
Father's attention shifted
entirely to him.

44
00:05:51,851 --> 00:05:53,811
That's enough.

45
00:05:55,897 --> 00:05:58,149
It does feel too eerie
to be a coincidence.

46
00:06:00,068 --> 00:06:02,403
Why is he back in Haeseong?
Didn't you ask him?

47
00:06:06,574 --> 00:06:08,242
He hurled a variant into the air.

48
00:06:09,660 --> 00:06:11,496
I think he was looking for something.

49
00:06:13,247 --> 00:06:14,582
What do you think?

50
00:06:16,459 --> 00:06:17,585
Do you think Father--

51
00:06:17,668 --> 00:06:18,836
Unlikely.

52
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:21,422
Father wouldn't call in others
without telling us.

53
00:06:22,465 --> 00:06:23,591
Would he?

54
00:06:25,593 --> 00:06:26,844
Haven't you heard anything?

55
00:06:28,596 --> 00:06:30,390
I'll look into it,

56
00:06:31,140 --> 00:06:32,975
so you two keep your mouths shut.

57
00:06:33,476 --> 00:06:34,560
About what?

58
00:06:38,606 --> 00:06:40,775
Another variant has appeared, Father.

59
00:06:40,858 --> 00:06:43,069
Then why are you still here?
Go collect it.

60
00:06:45,488 --> 00:06:46,531
Yes, Father.

61
00:07:02,046 --> 00:07:03,673
Something's fishy.

62
00:07:21,149 --> 00:07:22,108
Are you awake?

63
00:07:23,484 --> 00:07:26,362
You sure look peaceful
when you're passed out.

64
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:27,655
What

65
00:07:28,156 --> 00:07:28,990
is that?

66
00:07:29,907 --> 00:07:31,117
What happened?

67
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:32,743
I swear I threw it gently.

68
00:07:33,995 --> 00:07:36,914
But how on earth did the soda can
pierce a wall?

69
00:07:39,876 --> 00:07:41,085
Why am I here?

70
00:07:41,169 --> 00:07:45,465
Mr. Son left you here. He found you
passed out in the abandoned greenhouse.

71
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:01,731
Ro-bin, I think I…

72
00:08:01,814 --> 00:08:02,773
Yeah?

73
00:08:05,735 --> 00:08:07,528
It wasn't a near-death experience.

74
00:08:08,112 --> 00:08:09,405
Nor was it time travel.

75
00:08:09,489 --> 00:08:12,909
Of course it wasn't.
How could that possibly happen?

76
00:08:15,161 --> 00:08:16,537
It was teleportation.

77
00:08:49,028 --> 00:08:52,698
I finished all of today's deliveries,
so please stop being mad.

78
00:08:54,450 --> 00:08:59,080
What good is delivering
a 70th birthday congratulatory wreath

79
00:08:59,789 --> 00:09:01,165
after the party's over?

80
00:09:02,542 --> 00:09:04,752
Well wishes on their road to their 80th?

81
00:09:06,837 --> 00:09:10,675
I'm holding back because I don't want
to raise Cheong without a father,

82
00:09:10,758 --> 00:09:13,052
but I have limits, too, you know.

83
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:18,641
Look, I really was planning on
working very hard this morning,

84
00:09:18,724 --> 00:09:21,519
but my friend's father
passed away today, of all days.

85
00:09:22,353 --> 00:09:26,357
Everyone knows
that you don't have any friends.

86
00:09:27,483 --> 00:09:30,236
How do the fathers
of all those imaginary friends of yours

87
00:09:30,319 --> 00:09:32,321
manage to keep passing away?

88
00:09:33,739 --> 00:09:38,244
A lot of them are from blended families,
so naturally, they have two fathers.

89
00:09:43,124 --> 00:09:43,958
Aren't you coming?

90
00:09:44,709 --> 00:09:45,751
You go ahead.

91
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:48,170
I'll head home after wiping this down.

92
00:10:03,352 --> 00:10:04,437
Damn it.

93
00:10:06,022 --> 00:10:07,189
Oh, come on.

94
00:10:08,774 --> 00:10:10,651
Goddammit!

95
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:14,363
Damn it all!

96
00:10:14,447 --> 00:10:16,699
I'm not done wiping.
Did you forget something?

97
00:10:24,332 --> 00:10:26,083
I think a new variant has appeared.

98
00:10:27,251 --> 00:10:29,295
I need to know what's going on.

99
00:10:29,795 --> 00:10:30,880
Please contact me.

100
00:10:36,427 --> 00:10:37,261
DELETE

101
00:10:50,399 --> 00:10:51,651
What is it now?

102
00:10:52,234 --> 00:10:54,195
Something's strange with you, isn't it?

103
00:10:55,988 --> 00:10:57,031
What a load of bull.

104
00:10:58,866 --> 00:11:01,410
Did you see the hole
Ro-bin made in the wall with a can?

105
00:11:02,078 --> 00:11:03,746
And I keep vanishing into thin air.

106
00:11:03,829 --> 00:11:07,416
I zoom from place to place
in the blink of an eye.

107
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:10,544
Why are you barging into my shop
and spouting this nonsense?

108
00:11:10,628 --> 00:11:13,255
Do I look like I have time to waste
like you two? Leave!

109
00:11:13,756 --> 00:11:15,508
I have to finish wiping this pot.

110
00:11:15,591 --> 00:11:20,012
I swear I almost got shot earlier
in the middle of the ocean.

111
00:11:20,096 --> 00:11:21,514
Look, a bullet hole.

112
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:25,476
Are you okay? Is there nothing strange
going on with you?

113
00:11:27,186 --> 00:11:30,314
I'm so normal that I couldn't possibly be
more normal than I am now.

114
00:11:30,398 --> 00:11:33,401
So please don't lump me in
with the likes of you.

115
00:11:33,484 --> 00:11:36,320
I'm built differently from you two!

116
00:11:39,990 --> 00:11:40,908
The heck?

117
00:11:42,868 --> 00:11:44,787
What, are you stuck?

118
00:11:48,249 --> 00:11:50,543
You're stuck like glue, aren't you?

119
00:11:50,626 --> 00:11:52,211
Come on!

120
00:11:55,756 --> 00:11:58,008
Mr. Son, did you turn into flypaper?

121
00:11:58,092 --> 00:11:59,218
I told you I'm not--

122
00:12:04,014 --> 00:12:06,392
I think there's something wrong
with all of us.

123
00:12:06,892 --> 00:12:09,311
Maybe someone sprayed pesticide
in our neighborhood.

124
00:12:09,395 --> 00:12:11,564
Or perhaps they put a curse on us?

125
00:12:12,148 --> 00:12:13,941
Others would call these sorts of things

126
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:15,985
superpowers.

127
00:12:16,068 --> 00:12:17,403
No!

128
00:12:17,486 --> 00:12:19,363
Let's just call it a curse.

129
00:12:19,947 --> 00:12:21,574
Phenol. Yeah, that damn phenol!

130
00:12:22,366 --> 00:12:25,119
We've been cursed
by the 20th-century Industrial Revolution.

131
00:12:25,202 --> 00:12:26,370
These aren't superpowers!

132
00:12:26,454 --> 00:12:29,123
No! They're superpowers.

133
00:12:30,166 --> 00:12:32,001
There's no other explanation.

134
00:12:32,877 --> 00:12:34,128
This is insane!

135
00:12:34,211 --> 00:12:35,463
I knew something was wrong

136
00:12:35,963 --> 00:12:39,717
when I saw that pigeon's eyes
blinking sideways--

137
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:41,719
Don't do that!

138
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:45,097
You two. Not a peep about any of this.

139
00:12:45,181 --> 00:12:47,308
Your lips are sealed, no matter the cost.

140
00:12:47,391 --> 00:12:48,225
Why?

141
00:12:48,726 --> 00:12:51,103
Would we be carted away
and experimented on?

142
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:52,688
Wouldn't that be nice!

143
00:12:53,189 --> 00:12:56,650
People already call me a royal nightmare
for associating with you two.

144
00:12:56,734 --> 00:13:00,696
What would they think of me
if word got out that things stick to me?

145
00:13:01,197 --> 00:13:02,573
My daughter, Cheong…

146
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:04,742
And my darling Ms. Moon Mi-hui…

147
00:13:05,826 --> 00:13:07,828
I'm still Cheong's dad

148
00:13:08,329 --> 00:13:09,830
and the head of my household!

149
00:13:12,208 --> 00:13:14,627
I'll keep my family safe.

150
00:13:15,127 --> 00:13:16,212
You got that?

151
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:20,257
Is anyone here

152
00:13:21,091 --> 00:13:23,344
against you keeping your family safe?

153
00:13:23,427 --> 00:13:24,887
That's right, you punks!

154
00:13:24,970 --> 00:13:26,430
I'll keep my family safe,

155
00:13:26,514 --> 00:13:29,308
so you two stay quiet
and keep this a secret, okay?

156
00:13:31,227 --> 00:13:32,520
What exactly did you see?

157
00:13:32,603 --> 00:13:34,605
What? What do you mean, what did I see?

158
00:13:34,688 --> 00:13:36,649
You're freaking out right now.

159
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:40,778
What is it?
What's got you spooked? What did you see?

160
00:13:46,158 --> 00:13:47,368
Tell us!

161
00:13:47,451 --> 00:13:48,494
Hey.

162
00:13:48,577 --> 00:13:50,663
Or we'll just tell the whole neighborhood!

163
00:13:50,746 --> 00:13:53,499
Mr. Son, the Royal Nightmare,
has turned into human flypaper!

164
00:13:53,582 --> 00:13:54,708
Let go, damn it!

165
00:13:55,626 --> 00:13:56,836
You almost died!

166
00:13:58,879 --> 00:14:01,799
Mr. Oddball almost killed you!

167
00:14:10,766 --> 00:14:15,145
Yikes, look at those dark clouds
suddenly rolling in.

168
00:14:17,356 --> 00:14:21,735
In movies, doesn't something terrible
happen at moments like this?

169
00:14:33,455 --> 00:14:34,874
Please grab a ticket and wait--

170
00:14:39,003 --> 00:14:40,629
What brings you here today?

171
00:14:43,924 --> 00:14:45,676
Are you sure you want me to say

172
00:14:46,427 --> 00:14:47,636
what brought me here?

173
00:14:48,929 --> 00:14:49,763
Go ahead.

174
00:14:51,390 --> 00:14:54,977
What you did to me yesterday
in that abandoned greenhouse…

175
00:14:58,480 --> 00:15:02,776
I considered calling the cops,
but I figured I should hear you out first.

176
00:15:05,029 --> 00:15:06,906
I'm not sure what you're talking about.

177
00:15:08,616 --> 00:15:10,784
Then should I make it clearer for you?

178
00:15:10,868 --> 00:15:12,995
That thing you launched at me yesterday.

179
00:15:15,289 --> 00:15:16,290
Su…

180
00:15:18,334 --> 00:15:19,335
per…

181
00:15:20,794 --> 00:15:23,213
I'm sorry.
We can't help you with that here.

182
00:15:26,133 --> 00:15:27,593
Next, please!

183
00:15:30,220 --> 00:15:31,430
Next, please!

184
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:01,001
Shouldn't we help him?

185
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:04,129
Lady Trainwreck is too much
for a rookie to handle.

186
00:16:04,213 --> 00:16:05,422
We'll raise him strong.

187
00:16:05,506 --> 00:16:08,926
If Un-jeong overcomes this,
he will become a civil complaints master.

188
00:16:11,178 --> 00:16:12,513
Mr. Yang!

189
00:16:13,013 --> 00:16:14,848
Should I set up the main hall now?

190
00:16:14,932 --> 00:16:16,517
No, we'll do it this afternoon.

191
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:18,435
What about dog poop pickup at the park?

192
00:16:18,519 --> 00:16:20,854
Mr. Lee and Team A will take care of that.

193
00:16:20,938 --> 00:16:22,856
What about the street clean-up drive?

194
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:25,693
That's this Friday.
I told you to put a team together first.

195
00:16:25,776 --> 00:16:28,362
The area is too big
for one person to handle alone.

196
00:16:28,445 --> 00:16:29,697
Look here!

197
00:16:29,780 --> 00:16:32,825
Are all the Civil Complaints Office staff
away or something?

198
00:16:35,035 --> 00:16:38,080
In Haedeul-ri, Mr. Yang!
The complaint about the stench!

199
00:16:38,163 --> 00:16:40,749
It's far, and no vehicles
are available today.

200
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:42,668
The buses don't run often either.

201
00:16:42,751 --> 00:16:44,420
That's fine. I'll go.

202
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:46,296
Are you closed or what?

203
00:16:46,380 --> 00:16:48,298
Is this how you treat your visitors?

204
00:16:48,799 --> 00:16:49,717
All right, then.

205
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:53,095
First thing is to find the source
of the stench, so go. Hurry.

206
00:16:53,178 --> 00:16:54,972
- Go, quickly. Go on!
- Yes, sir.

207
00:16:57,850 --> 00:16:58,684
OUT ON BUSINESS

208
00:17:08,819 --> 00:17:10,237
Chae-ni will be okay, right?

209
00:17:10,821 --> 00:17:13,657
The city hall is packed.
He wouldn't try anything here.

210
00:17:20,122 --> 00:17:21,957
Mr. Son, quick! Start the car!

211
00:17:22,041 --> 00:17:23,292
Hey, what? Wait.

212
00:17:23,792 --> 00:17:25,294
Chae-ni, are you okay?

213
00:17:25,377 --> 00:17:26,712
Did he attack you at all?

214
00:17:26,795 --> 00:17:29,089
See if you still have
all your fingers and toes.

215
00:17:29,590 --> 00:17:32,593
If you're so worried,
why'd you let me go in alone?

216
00:17:32,676 --> 00:17:35,054
I tried to stop you.
You chose not to listen.

217
00:17:36,513 --> 00:17:37,973
What did City Hall Guy say?

218
00:17:38,057 --> 00:17:41,226
Why did he shoot that energy blast at you?
Is it really a superpower?

219
00:17:41,310 --> 00:17:42,686
Or is it some kind of disease?

220
00:17:42,770 --> 00:17:45,314
Why didn't you ask
whether we're just stuck with it

221
00:17:45,397 --> 00:17:49,234
or if the government has
some kind of plan or compensation?

222
00:17:49,318 --> 00:17:51,528
That's why I need you to tail him,
so I can ask!

223
00:17:51,612 --> 00:17:52,654
Fine.

224
00:17:53,238 --> 00:17:55,949
Go, hurry! That way, hurry!

225
00:17:56,033 --> 00:17:56,867
Step on it!

226
00:18:10,798 --> 00:18:14,259
We contacted you, ma'am,
because his entire family is abroad.

227
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:16,762
A suicide note was found at the scene.

228
00:18:17,346 --> 00:18:18,764
It was addressed to you.

229
00:18:19,348 --> 00:18:20,307
A suicide note?

230
00:18:22,810 --> 00:18:24,853
You mean that
Director Choi committed suicide?

231
00:18:29,441 --> 00:18:30,567
Why don't you read it?

232
00:18:32,903 --> 00:18:34,780
TO MS. KIM JEON-BOK

233
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:42,329
Dr. Ha Won-do is innocent.

234
00:18:43,038 --> 00:18:45,124
He was an honorable scholar.

235
00:18:45,958 --> 00:18:48,418
You people are the ones who have sinned.

236
00:18:48,961 --> 00:18:51,255
May you beg Dr. Ha Won-do for forgiveness.

237
00:18:59,096 --> 00:19:00,472
Director Choi.

238
00:19:01,431 --> 00:19:03,225
Let me ask you one last time.

239
00:19:05,102 --> 00:19:07,146
Where is the Child of Eternity?

240
00:19:14,945 --> 00:19:16,280
Answer him.

241
00:19:29,543 --> 00:19:30,961
Hearty House…

242
00:19:34,256 --> 00:19:35,340
Madam King.

243
00:20:13,670 --> 00:20:18,133
Early this morning, there was an explosion
at an orphanage in Haeseong.

244
00:20:18,217 --> 00:20:20,844
The fire department
responded immediately to the call,

245
00:20:20,928 --> 00:20:24,431
but the flames were difficult
to extinguish.

246
00:20:24,514 --> 00:20:28,518
While searching the charred orphanage,
the fire department and police…

247
00:20:28,602 --> 00:20:32,147
The children discovered in the lab
are currently in treatment

248
00:20:32,231 --> 00:20:33,941
with relevant government support.

249
00:20:34,024 --> 00:20:38,403
The chief of the lab is Dr. Ha Won-do,
a specialist in cell regeneration.

250
00:20:38,487 --> 00:20:41,448
He is suspected
of conducting illegal clinical trials

251
00:20:41,531 --> 00:20:43,200
on the children at the orphanage.

252
00:20:43,283 --> 00:20:45,744
The police stated
they will investigate the researchers

253
00:20:45,827 --> 00:20:48,080
who were involved in the experiments.

254
00:20:48,163 --> 00:20:50,207
Dr. Ha Won-do! Please say a few words!

255
00:20:50,290 --> 00:20:51,625
- Stand back!
- Dr. Ha Won-do!

256
00:20:53,252 --> 00:20:54,127
THE HOLY BIBLE

257
00:21:14,106 --> 00:21:15,148
Hello, ma'am.

258
00:21:15,732 --> 00:21:16,817
Can I help you?

259
00:21:16,900 --> 00:21:18,819
We've received a missing persons report.

260
00:21:28,787 --> 00:21:31,206
Even family members
often struggle to see eye to eye

261
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:33,542
when they follow different religions.

262
00:21:35,377 --> 00:21:37,713
But to claim that we imprison runaways…

263
00:21:38,255 --> 00:21:40,007
That's just ridiculous.

264
00:21:42,342 --> 00:21:46,221
Everyone here has come
of their own free will.

265
00:21:46,305 --> 00:21:50,809
We're obligated to check out all reports.
Thank you for understanding.

266
00:21:52,144 --> 00:21:53,270
Please take your time.

267
00:22:01,361 --> 00:22:03,739
This place is huge.

268
00:22:04,698 --> 00:22:07,951
- Anyway, thank you for your cooperation.
- Oh, it's nothing.

269
00:22:10,203 --> 00:22:12,039
Is there a basement here?

270
00:22:17,502 --> 00:22:18,754
Would you like a look?

271
00:22:34,102 --> 00:22:35,937
Just look at you.

272
00:22:36,605 --> 00:22:37,773
Kim Bong-pal.

273
00:22:38,273 --> 00:22:40,609
I never got to pay back your 5,000 won.

274
00:22:44,946 --> 00:22:45,947
It's the police!

275
00:22:46,740 --> 00:22:48,158
Officers!

276
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:50,077
Mr. Officer!

277
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:53,372
Here! Please save me!

278
00:22:54,039 --> 00:22:57,709
This is an area we've set up
for our believers to rest.

279
00:23:13,683 --> 00:23:14,726
Wow.

280
00:23:20,399 --> 00:23:23,276
It must have cost a fortune
to set this up.

281
00:23:28,448 --> 00:23:31,076
These tropical fish look expensive too.

282
00:23:32,411 --> 00:23:34,246
I saw them in a picture book as a kid.

283
00:23:35,455 --> 00:23:36,289
Sorry?

284
00:23:39,459 --> 00:23:40,877
Right, I see.

285
00:23:49,594 --> 00:23:51,763
Here, I'm in here.

286
00:23:51,847 --> 00:23:54,766
Please get me out of here!

287
00:23:54,850 --> 00:23:56,601
Hey, Mr. Police Officer!

288
00:23:57,978 --> 00:23:58,937
I'm over here!

289
00:23:59,020 --> 00:24:01,231
Hey!

290
00:24:01,314 --> 00:24:04,317
Hey, get me out of here!

291
00:24:04,401 --> 00:24:05,902
That's it. Over here.

292
00:24:06,903 --> 00:24:08,488
Here!

293
00:24:08,989 --> 00:24:10,031
This way!

294
00:24:10,115 --> 00:24:12,117
Where are you looking? I said here!

295
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:13,910
Yes, that's it.

296
00:24:14,536 --> 00:24:15,579
Get me out.

297
00:24:23,879 --> 00:24:24,754
Here!

298
00:24:25,255 --> 00:24:27,007
Get me out. Hey, what…

299
00:24:27,507 --> 00:24:30,260
I said get me out of here! Please!

300
00:24:31,011 --> 00:24:33,430
Would you like to look around some more?

301
00:24:33,513 --> 00:24:34,848
Hello?

302
00:24:35,682 --> 00:24:38,143
No, I think we've seen more than enough.

303
00:24:38,226 --> 00:24:39,311
Let's go.

304
00:24:39,394 --> 00:24:40,437
Yes, sir.

305
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:41,396
If you say so.

306
00:24:42,606 --> 00:24:45,567
No, don't go!

307
00:24:45,650 --> 00:24:47,444
Please help me!

308
00:24:47,527 --> 00:24:50,030
Hey, you!

309
00:24:51,031 --> 00:24:53,158
Help me!

310
00:24:59,206 --> 00:25:02,292
Doesn't the next bus to Haedeul-ri
come in two hours?

311
00:25:02,375 --> 00:25:04,628
Yeah, and the forecast said
it'll rain today.

312
00:25:04,711 --> 00:25:06,546
Oh dear, looks like it's going to pour.

313
00:25:06,630 --> 00:25:08,965
My questions are about to pour out too.

314
00:25:09,508 --> 00:25:10,926
About the phenol poisoning

315
00:25:11,009 --> 00:25:12,886
and whether we're just stuck with it,

316
00:25:12,969 --> 00:25:16,139
or if there's some kind of plan
or compensation from the government.

317
00:25:18,058 --> 00:25:21,228
We have all the time in the world.
How about a game of acrostics?

318
00:25:21,311 --> 00:25:22,270
- Sure.
- I'm in.

319
00:25:22,354 --> 00:25:23,438
Start me off.

320
00:25:23,522 --> 00:25:25,273
How about… Su!

321
00:25:25,857 --> 00:25:26,983
Super spooked.

322
00:25:27,067 --> 00:25:27,901
Per…

323
00:25:27,984 --> 00:25:29,110
Perplexing powers.

324
00:25:29,945 --> 00:25:30,946
Power!

325
00:25:34,574 --> 00:25:36,618
Powerful predicament, eh?

326
00:25:39,079 --> 00:25:40,956
Not bad. Hey, careful with that knife.

327
00:25:41,039 --> 00:25:43,124
I have one too. Kang Ro-bin, hit me.

328
00:25:43,208 --> 00:25:44,042
Su!

329
00:25:44,125 --> 00:25:45,460
Super anxious, aren't you?

330
00:25:46,044 --> 00:25:46,878
Per!

331
00:25:46,962 --> 00:25:49,214
Perhaps because we found out
you have superpowers.

332
00:25:49,965 --> 00:25:50,799
Power!

333
00:25:51,675 --> 00:25:53,677
Powerful predicament, eh?

334
00:25:55,011 --> 00:25:56,805
Hey, don't wave that knife around.

335
00:25:58,598 --> 00:26:00,559
I said be careful. You'll hurt someone.

336
00:26:00,642 --> 00:26:01,685
High-five!

337
00:26:03,812 --> 00:26:06,940
What? Thinking of shooting
another energy blast at me?

338
00:26:07,524 --> 00:26:10,068
Don't provoke him.
He might blast you to smithereens.

339
00:26:11,653 --> 00:26:15,156
Let's see you try, then.
We won't back down that easily.

340
00:26:15,240 --> 00:26:16,074
Sure.

341
00:26:16,575 --> 00:26:17,659
I'll back down, then.

342
00:26:20,620 --> 00:26:22,372
Ms. Eun Chae-ni. Excuse me!

343
00:26:22,455 --> 00:26:24,416
My bag! Ms. Eun Chae-ni!

344
00:26:27,085 --> 00:26:28,837
Ms. Eun Chae-ni. Give me--

345
00:26:29,337 --> 00:26:31,089
What the… Mr. Kang Ro-bin.

346
00:26:31,590 --> 00:26:32,924
What do you think you're--

347
00:26:34,718 --> 00:26:39,347
CHURCH OF ETERNAL SALVATION

348
00:26:53,320 --> 00:26:54,863
I'm glad that ended well.

349
00:26:55,739 --> 00:26:58,992
Getting mixed up with religious groups
is always a headache.

350
00:27:00,910 --> 00:27:03,622
What's this stuff you've had on
since yesterday?

351
00:27:03,705 --> 00:27:06,875
I didn't put anything on.
I've just been sweating the past few days.

352
00:27:11,379 --> 00:27:14,507
Hey, this isn't sweat!
You've covered yourself in something!

353
00:27:14,591 --> 00:27:16,259
I'm telling you, it's sweat.

354
00:27:18,428 --> 00:27:21,306
- Maybe I ate something odd.
- Let's get going.

355
00:27:35,862 --> 00:27:38,823
- My heart's healthier.
- Can someone like me gain superpowers too?

356
00:27:38,907 --> 00:27:41,284
- Will I stay healthy?
- Uri Geller, the magic guy…

357
00:27:41,368 --> 00:27:43,328
- Will we be vivisected?
- Or lose our powers?

358
00:27:43,411 --> 00:27:45,455
- He earned a fortune.
- How come I'm healthier?

359
00:27:45,538 --> 00:27:46,873
In this economy, you need to…

360
00:27:46,956 --> 00:27:48,708
- I just don't get why--
- Excuse me.

361
00:27:50,502 --> 00:27:52,420
I can't hear a word you're saying.

362
00:27:52,921 --> 00:27:55,340
If you all talk at once,
how can I understand--

363
00:27:55,423 --> 00:27:59,052
We've told you earlier
that all three of us now have superpowers.

364
00:27:59,135 --> 00:28:01,596
Mr. Son sticks to things.
He busts holes in walls.

365
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:03,348
And I teleport in a flash.

366
00:28:04,641 --> 00:28:06,393
I still can't understand you.

367
00:28:06,476 --> 00:28:09,938
Look here. Do you really think
I didn't see anything?

368
00:28:10,647 --> 00:28:12,107
That thing you did…

369
00:28:12,190 --> 00:28:14,275
You're not Mr. Oddball
but Mr. Energy Blast.

370
00:28:14,359 --> 00:28:17,237
You seemed to control your power at will.

371
00:28:17,320 --> 00:28:21,658
The least you can do is tell us
how to control ours too.

372
00:28:21,741 --> 00:28:25,537
Yes, sir, please tell us.
We're all going to be okay, right?

373
00:28:26,538 --> 00:28:27,997
I'm terrified.

374
00:28:31,251 --> 00:28:32,377
Look.

375
00:28:36,381 --> 00:28:38,925
I thought you'd use your powers
in a pinch. Guess not.

376
00:28:39,008 --> 00:28:41,511
You're slower than you look.

377
00:28:41,594 --> 00:28:43,596
You just wanted to throw that at me.

378
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:44,681
Okay, fine.

379
00:28:45,181 --> 00:28:47,517
I won't ask you to demonstrate.

380
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:50,061
Just tell me what's going on here.

381
00:28:50,937 --> 00:28:54,274
Then I'll forget about you blasting me
with your energy.

382
00:28:54,774 --> 00:28:57,986
If you tell me everything,
I'll even call you Master.

383
00:29:01,489 --> 00:29:04,409
I don't know what you saw
and what misconception you have,

384
00:29:04,909 --> 00:29:08,413
but I don't think I can help you
with this complaint. I'm sorry.

385
00:29:11,207 --> 00:29:14,836
So, you're telling us
to figure this out by ourselves.

386
00:29:19,090 --> 00:29:20,008
Yes.

387
00:29:22,802 --> 00:29:23,803
- That's it.
- Get out.

388
00:29:23,887 --> 00:29:26,598
You kidnapped me.
You can't just ditch me like--

389
00:29:26,681 --> 00:29:27,974
Where are we, anyway?

390
00:29:29,142 --> 00:29:30,769
At least tell me where we are!

391
00:29:30,852 --> 00:29:32,020
Deary me, what a shame.

392
00:29:32,103 --> 00:29:34,814
I don't think
I can help you with that question.

393
00:29:34,898 --> 00:29:37,901
Kang Ro-bin, what are you doing?
Man, this guy won't give up!

394
00:29:38,735 --> 00:29:40,487
Man, he's strong.

395
00:29:43,573 --> 00:29:44,824
What the…

396
00:29:44,908 --> 00:29:47,702
Hey, Gyeong-hwan!

397
00:29:47,786 --> 00:29:48,620
Gyeong-hwan!

398
00:29:48,703 --> 00:29:50,163
What's wrong with you, man?

399
00:29:50,246 --> 00:29:51,539
Snap out of it!

400
00:29:51,623 --> 00:29:53,625
Hey, Gyeong-hwan!

401
00:30:02,217 --> 00:30:06,387
- It's smoking. Watch out for the glass!
- What if it explodes soon?

402
00:30:06,471 --> 00:30:10,225
- Okay, three, two, one!
- Quick, hurry!

403
00:30:10,725 --> 00:30:12,268
Let's help him up first.

404
00:30:12,352 --> 00:30:13,978
- Hurry!
- That's it!

405
00:30:14,062 --> 00:30:15,772
Is he conscious or what?

406
00:30:15,855 --> 00:30:17,565
I guess not. Hurry!

407
00:30:17,649 --> 00:30:18,483
Go, yeah.

408
00:30:19,776 --> 00:30:20,777
He weighs a ton.

409
00:30:23,154 --> 00:30:26,199
Mister, your hand! Darn, I can't reach.

410
00:30:27,492 --> 00:30:29,452
Ro-bin! Kang Ro-bin, get over here!

411
00:30:32,580 --> 00:30:34,457
Man, this is scary. Really scary.

412
00:30:34,541 --> 00:30:35,625
Hey, mister.

413
00:30:35,708 --> 00:30:37,210
Wake up, will you?

414
00:30:37,293 --> 00:30:39,254
Are you dead? That's not good.

415
00:30:42,841 --> 00:30:44,509
Why's his arm like this?

416
00:30:45,343 --> 00:30:46,219
Is it broken?

417
00:30:46,302 --> 00:30:47,929
- This is…
- He's so sweaty.

418
00:30:48,012 --> 00:30:49,597
What is this?

419
00:30:49,681 --> 00:30:52,267
- Hey, mister! Be careful.
- We need to save him!

420
00:30:52,767 --> 00:30:54,435
Quick.

421
00:31:02,527 --> 00:31:04,070
We'll get him from below.

422
00:31:05,405 --> 00:31:06,614
- Fire!
- There's a fire!

423
00:31:06,698 --> 00:31:08,366
Step back. It's dangerous!

424
00:31:09,075 --> 00:31:09,909
What do we do?

425
00:31:11,411 --> 00:31:13,121
Those two never goddamn listen!

426
00:31:14,080 --> 00:31:14,914
Push.

427
00:31:16,124 --> 00:31:17,375
What are you doing?

428
00:31:17,458 --> 00:31:19,377
Are you gonna just stand there and watch?

429
00:31:26,134 --> 00:31:28,303
Are you really not going to help us?

430
00:31:28,386 --> 00:31:32,140
Why be stingy with your powers?
Gonna buy a house with them or something?

431
00:31:32,223 --> 00:31:34,809
Are you sure you even have a superpower?

432
00:31:34,893 --> 00:31:38,146
Hey, stop that and get over here!
It's going to blow!

433
00:31:38,229 --> 00:31:40,940
First responders will be here soon.
Why are you doing that?

434
00:31:41,024 --> 00:31:44,360
It's always the reckless ones
who have to make everything a production.

435
00:31:44,444 --> 00:31:48,239
Do you always have to be so insufferable?

436
00:31:49,574 --> 00:31:52,368
At least go get some water
to put out the fire!

437
00:31:54,913 --> 00:31:56,581
Where am I supposed to get water?

438
00:31:56,664 --> 00:32:00,627
I'm not doing this because you told me to.
It's for the public good, okay?

439
00:32:02,170 --> 00:32:04,756
I guess I'll have to walk around.

440
00:32:07,842 --> 00:32:09,510
It won't budge.

441
00:32:30,823 --> 00:32:32,742
Hey, Chae-ni, I got my strength back!

442
00:32:35,745 --> 00:32:37,622
I… I'm…

443
00:32:39,666 --> 00:32:40,792
I'm…

444
00:32:41,376 --> 00:32:42,877
I'm useful now!

445
00:32:43,461 --> 00:32:45,171
Now that I have this power,

446
00:32:45,922 --> 00:32:47,840
I'm useful, Chae-ni!

447
00:32:47,924 --> 00:32:49,759
Wow, yeah.

448
00:32:49,842 --> 00:32:52,011
You're amazing, Kang Ro-bin!

449
00:32:54,180 --> 00:32:56,474
Keep using your powers,
the amazing Kang Ro-bin.

450
00:32:57,308 --> 00:32:58,226
Okay.

451
00:33:00,937 --> 00:33:04,023
Who taught her
to speak so disrespectfully?

452
00:33:10,405 --> 00:33:11,698
You bastard!

453
00:33:43,688 --> 00:33:45,023
I'll save you, mister.

454
00:33:45,106 --> 00:33:47,525
But what is this? Why is he so slippery?

455
00:33:47,608 --> 00:33:49,527
Mister, you're still alive, right?

456
00:33:49,610 --> 00:33:50,778
You'd better be.

457
00:33:50,862 --> 00:33:52,238
You can't die, mister.

458
00:33:52,321 --> 00:33:54,407
Even if you can't come to your senses…

459
00:33:54,490 --> 00:33:56,492
You're badly hurt. Oh no, what do we do?

460
00:34:11,257 --> 00:34:12,633
Great job, Kang Ro-bin.

461
00:34:13,885 --> 00:34:15,595
You were pretty darn cool.

462
00:34:19,015 --> 00:34:19,974
A carp!

463
00:34:20,475 --> 00:34:21,309
Guys!

464
00:34:21,392 --> 00:34:23,770
I saw a carp…
Why are his arms so freaking long?

465
00:34:23,853 --> 00:34:26,064
Just put out the fire already!

466
00:34:33,362 --> 00:34:34,614
Hey, a carp…

467
00:34:35,114 --> 00:34:36,824
A carp as big as me

468
00:34:36,908 --> 00:34:39,577
looked my way, then flashed me a wink.

469
00:34:39,660 --> 00:34:43,039
Mr. Son, I just lifted this car.

470
00:34:43,122 --> 00:34:46,209
I'm dead serious!
I really saw a carp as big as me.

471
00:34:46,292 --> 00:34:49,087
It even had lashes on its eyelids!

472
00:34:49,170 --> 00:34:51,589
Funny how you're the only one
who sees these things.

473
00:34:51,672 --> 00:34:53,049
What are the odds?

474
00:34:54,383 --> 00:34:56,511
Are you calling me a liar right now?

475
00:34:57,178 --> 00:34:59,722
I've never lied in my entire life.
How dare you…

476
00:35:02,058 --> 00:35:03,309
What's going on here?

477
00:35:07,563 --> 00:35:08,439
Now?

478
00:35:13,694 --> 00:35:14,654
Of all times…

479
00:35:17,073 --> 00:35:19,742
Mr. Son, what are you doing? Let go of me!

480
00:35:19,826 --> 00:35:22,036
Hey, I really want to let go too.

481
00:35:23,162 --> 00:35:24,747
What? Are they stuck?

482
00:35:25,414 --> 00:35:26,290
No way.

483
00:35:26,791 --> 00:35:27,625
For real?

484
00:35:31,337 --> 00:35:32,171
Damn it!

485
00:35:32,255 --> 00:35:35,049
Get it off. Hurry! Pull it off!

486
00:35:35,133 --> 00:35:37,301
How are you meant to get it off?

487
00:35:37,385 --> 00:35:39,929
No, get off!

488
00:35:40,012 --> 00:35:40,930
This can't be.

489
00:35:41,597 --> 00:35:42,473
Get off!

490
00:35:42,974 --> 00:35:43,891
Get off!

491
00:35:45,143 --> 00:35:46,727
Aren't you gonna do something?

492
00:35:46,811 --> 00:35:48,855
At this rate, they'll be roasted whole!

493
00:35:53,693 --> 00:35:56,445
Seriously, do something, Mr. Son!

494
00:35:57,572 --> 00:35:59,574
What the…
Mr. Oddball, what did you just do?

495
00:35:59,657 --> 00:36:01,325
If you're doing it, do it right!

496
00:36:01,409 --> 00:36:03,953
Do you really even have a superpower?

497
00:36:05,329 --> 00:36:07,999
Come on, what are you doing?
The fire's spreading!

498
00:36:08,082 --> 00:36:10,126
Get Mr. Son off of there already!

499
00:36:29,061 --> 00:36:31,189
What about me?

500
00:36:32,356 --> 00:36:33,399
Mr. Son!

501
00:36:33,983 --> 00:36:36,319
- Get to safety now!
- What about you, Mr. Son?

502
00:36:36,402 --> 00:36:39,947
There's no way I'm dying here.
No way in hell!

503
00:36:40,489 --> 00:36:43,492
So get to safety now, you little shit!

504
00:36:43,576 --> 00:36:45,328
You never goddamn listen!

505
00:36:46,412 --> 00:36:47,246
Mr. Son.

506
00:36:49,832 --> 00:36:50,958
No way.

507
00:36:51,459 --> 00:36:53,085
Is Mr. Son really going to die?

508
00:36:56,505 --> 00:37:00,009
That's not right!
After all the miserable things he's done?

509
00:37:01,928 --> 00:37:03,137
I won't let that happen.

510
00:37:03,888 --> 00:37:06,015
If you die, it'll be by my hands--

511
00:37:09,727 --> 00:37:11,479
Mr. Son!

512
00:37:11,562 --> 00:37:12,939
Get away!

513
00:37:19,278 --> 00:37:20,196
I said go!

514
00:37:20,780 --> 00:37:23,741
Go get someone else. Anyone but you.

515
00:37:24,325 --> 00:37:27,912
What are you… Just hurry up and go.

516
00:37:27,995 --> 00:37:30,164
I could do it just moments ago.

517
00:37:30,248 --> 00:37:33,209
I had a superpower too!

518
00:37:34,669 --> 00:37:38,881
At this rate, we'll both die!

519
00:37:39,799 --> 00:37:41,592
Why does it have to be you?

520
00:37:42,343 --> 00:37:45,054
Why are you the one here with me
at a moment like this?

521
00:37:45,137 --> 00:37:49,892
Why you, the most useless person
in the entire world?

522
00:37:49,976 --> 00:37:52,561
I told you to stop being so mean!

523
00:38:00,278 --> 00:38:01,237
Try that again?

524
00:38:09,578 --> 00:38:10,579
Fire!

525
00:38:31,559 --> 00:38:33,227
Let's cut his arm off with this!

526
00:38:37,315 --> 00:38:38,441
You're alive?

527
00:38:41,360 --> 00:38:42,445
Hey!

528
00:38:42,945 --> 00:38:44,071
You're alive!

529
00:38:45,031 --> 00:38:46,699
Kang Ro-bin, you…

530
00:38:47,908 --> 00:38:48,743
You…

531
00:38:51,787 --> 00:38:53,289
That's right, Mr. Son.

532
00:38:53,914 --> 00:38:55,958
I saved your life.

533
00:38:57,418 --> 00:38:59,128
You have phenol poisoning too.

534
00:39:00,254 --> 00:39:01,922
Phenol, for sure…

535
00:39:09,805 --> 00:39:12,516
So we saved them?

536
00:39:15,811 --> 00:39:16,979
Wow.

537
00:39:17,063 --> 00:39:18,773
We're

538
00:39:19,273 --> 00:39:21,734
pretty awesome, aren't we?

539
00:39:40,044 --> 00:39:41,420
Just look at those flames.

540
00:39:44,423 --> 00:39:45,508
Here's your water.

541
00:39:49,762 --> 00:39:51,555
Any news on what I asked you to check?

542
00:39:53,015 --> 00:39:55,518
Director Choi's vacation home
had security cameras,

543
00:39:56,018 --> 00:39:57,937
but all the footage was erased.

544
00:39:58,646 --> 00:40:00,064
They think someone took it.

545
00:40:00,147 --> 00:40:02,274
And they have no idea
who it might've been?

546
00:40:03,609 --> 00:40:07,822
There were no fingerprints or traces.
Even the police are baffled.

547
00:40:08,864 --> 00:40:11,992
Shouldn't you close the restaurant
for a while and go into hiding?

548
00:40:13,244 --> 00:40:15,955
Four people involved in this
are already dead.

549
00:40:16,539 --> 00:40:17,623
Check, please.

550
00:40:18,124 --> 00:40:18,958
Of course.

551
00:40:23,462 --> 00:40:24,463
FLOWERS

552
00:40:31,262 --> 00:40:34,306
But what was up with that cop earlier?

553
00:40:34,932 --> 00:40:38,477
Do you think turning into a floppy monster
is also a superpower?

554
00:40:38,561 --> 00:40:41,063
It means we're not the only ones
who are messed up.

555
00:40:41,147 --> 00:40:43,149
Pigeons, carp,

556
00:40:43,649 --> 00:40:45,359
and now even those cops.

557
00:40:45,443 --> 00:40:48,237
It's proof that our entire town
is getting sick.

558
00:40:51,490 --> 00:40:52,700
So what should we do now?

559
00:40:54,076 --> 00:40:55,411
Why are you asking me?

560
00:40:56,370 --> 00:40:58,789
We've all seen each other's superpowers.

561
00:40:58,873 --> 00:41:00,249
Doesn't that make us a team?

562
00:41:00,332 --> 00:41:01,959
- A team?
- A team?

563
00:41:02,042 --> 00:41:05,713
We saved those two cops, didn't we?
By working together as a team.

564
00:41:05,796 --> 00:41:08,215
We did risk our lives
for zero financial gain.

565
00:41:08,966 --> 00:41:10,134
Wait a minute.

566
00:41:11,719 --> 00:41:14,597
Do you think we could get
some reward money for that?

567
00:41:15,556 --> 00:41:17,808
Whoa, reward money!

568
00:41:17,892 --> 00:41:19,185
Hey, that hurts.

569
00:41:19,268 --> 00:41:23,105
First thing we can do is split that money
four ways. What do you say, City Hall Guy?

570
00:41:23,189 --> 00:41:25,608
No, I'm done here.

571
00:41:32,490 --> 00:41:35,242
You three can deal with
what happened to you on your own.

572
00:41:35,326 --> 00:41:37,286
I don't know what you want from me,

573
00:41:37,369 --> 00:41:39,413
but even if I did, I couldn't help you.

574
00:41:40,289 --> 00:41:41,749
Nor do I care to.

575
00:41:53,844 --> 00:41:57,223
What's he giving us the cold shoulder for?

576
00:41:57,306 --> 00:41:58,307
How heartless.

577
00:41:58,891 --> 00:42:00,684
I guess he really doesn't like us.

578
00:42:00,768 --> 00:42:02,228
Who would?

579
00:42:06,190 --> 00:42:08,192
That's one less mouth to feed though.

580
00:42:08,692 --> 00:42:10,653
About the reward money.

581
00:42:11,529 --> 00:42:13,239
I guess we'll split it three ways?

582
00:42:18,160 --> 00:42:18,994
Shall we?

583
00:42:58,492 --> 00:43:00,160
HAESEONG DRAINAGE PLANS

584
00:43:07,960 --> 00:43:09,336
GYEGO-1-DONG DRAINAGE PLAN

585
00:43:11,964 --> 00:43:12,798
GYEGO-2-DONG

586
00:43:12,881 --> 00:43:14,091
HAEDEUL-RI DRAINAGE PLAN

587
00:43:25,311 --> 00:43:27,021
STORMWATER SEWER WINGWALL

588
00:43:48,751 --> 00:43:49,877
"13 Haedeul-ri."

589
00:43:50,836 --> 00:43:52,171
13 Haedeul-ri…

590
00:44:01,263 --> 00:44:02,723
13 Haejeon-eup.

591
00:44:04,516 --> 00:44:07,770
CHURCH OF ETERNAL SALVATION
PRAYER HOUSE

592
00:44:20,324 --> 00:44:22,368
- They're not here?
- How could that be?

593
00:44:23,285 --> 00:44:24,828
They were never even admitted.

594
00:44:24,912 --> 00:44:27,748
No police officers
were brought here today.

595
00:44:27,831 --> 00:44:29,124
Nurse Eom?

596
00:44:29,208 --> 00:44:31,043
Yes, I'm coming!

597
00:44:35,506 --> 00:44:38,008
Didn't they clearly say Haeseong Hospital?

598
00:44:38,092 --> 00:44:40,052
But she said they never came here.

599
00:45:00,739 --> 00:45:02,991
What do you mean you never got the report?

600
00:45:03,492 --> 00:45:05,661
We definitely reported it.

601
00:45:06,161 --> 00:45:08,539
There was a car accident,
then an ambulance came

602
00:45:08,622 --> 00:45:11,917
and took the two injured cops
to Haeseong Hospital.

603
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:13,419
Maybe you were mistaken.

604
00:45:13,502 --> 00:45:17,047
We have no record of a report from
or dispatch to Haedeul-ri.

605
00:45:17,589 --> 00:45:20,008
And no car accidents
involving police officers.

606
00:45:22,803 --> 00:45:24,012
What is going on?

607
00:45:24,680 --> 00:45:26,348
If there's no record of a report,

608
00:45:26,432 --> 00:45:29,768
who were those paramedics
who took the cops?

609
00:45:30,686 --> 00:45:32,271
Then the cops who were injured,

610
00:45:32,771 --> 00:45:34,481
where did they disappear to?

611
00:45:34,565 --> 00:45:35,649
They must have

612
00:45:36,442 --> 00:45:41,071
been taken by people
who don't want this to get out.

613
00:45:41,822 --> 00:45:45,617
Does that mean if they find out about us,
they'll come and take us too?

614
00:45:45,701 --> 00:45:46,660
Where to?

615
00:45:47,536 --> 00:45:48,412
What if

616
00:45:48,912 --> 00:45:50,789
we get taken somewhere, too,

617
00:45:50,873 --> 00:45:52,750
to get vivisected or something?

618
00:45:52,833 --> 00:45:56,086
Damn. They should at least
put us under first.

619
00:45:56,587 --> 00:45:58,839
I'm scared. Chae-ni, I'm freaking out.

620
00:46:06,388 --> 00:46:07,473
RELIGIOUS FACILITIES

621
00:46:09,057 --> 00:46:11,977
This has nothing to do with me.
Nothing at all.

622
00:47:03,362 --> 00:47:05,239
This area's restricted to staff only.

623
00:47:05,322 --> 00:47:06,615
In life,

624
00:47:07,574 --> 00:47:10,953
people can sometimes lose their way.

625
00:47:12,371 --> 00:47:14,164
They go to places they shouldn't

626
00:47:14,998 --> 00:47:17,042
and look for things they shouldn't.

627
00:47:17,626 --> 00:47:19,586
Unaware that it'll cost them their lives.

628
00:47:21,421 --> 00:47:23,340
Isn't that right, 3972?

629
00:47:30,222 --> 00:47:31,056
Here?

630
00:47:32,266 --> 00:47:34,476
There'd be a lot of casualties.

631
00:47:35,394 --> 00:47:36,353
You okay with that?

632
00:47:42,234 --> 00:47:43,944
Hey, Mr. Lee Un-jeong.

633
00:47:44,027 --> 00:47:47,197
There you are. Talk about great timing.

634
00:47:47,281 --> 00:47:49,992
Can you hurry and set up the partitions
in the main hall?

635
00:47:50,075 --> 00:47:52,828
I have to prep for tomorrow's meeting,
so I don't have time.

636
00:47:54,204 --> 00:47:55,038
Okay, sir.

637
00:47:55,622 --> 00:47:57,374
Great, well…

638
00:47:58,375 --> 00:48:00,711
Where has Mr. Lee Sang-min gone now?

639
00:48:04,965 --> 00:48:06,383
Mr. Lee Un-jeong?

640
00:48:08,010 --> 00:48:10,429
You seem busy, so I'll get to the point.

641
00:48:14,808 --> 00:48:16,727
Why are you back in Haeseong?

642
00:48:16,810 --> 00:48:18,854
Why would a civil servant need a reason?

643
00:48:19,521 --> 00:48:21,273
You go wherever you're assigned.

644
00:48:21,356 --> 00:48:23,233
Did Father…

645
00:48:26,361 --> 00:48:27,487
call you here?

646
00:48:27,571 --> 00:48:28,739
Father?

647
00:48:32,117 --> 00:48:34,828
You still call the man
who made you this way "Father"?

648
00:48:34,912 --> 00:48:37,414
Of course, because he made me this way.

649
00:48:38,498 --> 00:48:39,458
From the weak,

650
00:48:39,958 --> 00:48:41,209
useless,

651
00:48:41,710 --> 00:48:44,254
unwanted Number 4885,

652
00:48:45,339 --> 00:48:47,382
he made me into the Kim Pal-ho I am today.

653
00:48:49,384 --> 00:48:51,470
Father made me feel needed.

654
00:48:52,471 --> 00:48:53,597
He made me strong.

655
00:48:53,680 --> 00:48:56,600
He made you into a monster and used you.

656
00:48:57,184 --> 00:48:58,226
Back then

657
00:48:58,810 --> 00:48:59,645
and now.

658
00:49:01,813 --> 00:49:06,109
I won't bother asking what you
and Dr. Ha Won-do are up to in Haedeul-ri.

659
00:49:06,193 --> 00:49:09,863
I'm not particularly interested,
and I'd rather not get involved.

660
00:49:12,032 --> 00:49:13,200
But don't you think

661
00:49:13,283 --> 00:49:15,369
continuing to create more variants

662
00:49:15,953 --> 00:49:17,287
would be a problem?

663
00:49:19,665 --> 00:49:20,999
Don't you worry.

664
00:49:22,125 --> 00:49:24,920
We're already quietly collecting
the defective ones.

665
00:49:26,421 --> 00:49:27,255
Collecting?

666
00:49:27,339 --> 00:49:29,883
To cleanse the world
and make it beautiful.

667
00:49:33,053 --> 00:49:34,096
Don't you know

668
00:49:34,596 --> 00:49:36,807
that you and I are just like them?

669
00:49:37,933 --> 00:49:38,767
Defects.

670
00:49:40,435 --> 00:49:41,561
No!

671
00:49:42,521 --> 00:49:44,106
We're not.

672
00:49:44,648 --> 00:49:47,275
Why do you think
he called us Wunderkinder?

673
00:49:47,359 --> 00:49:49,611
Because we're miracles, not failures!

674
00:49:49,695 --> 00:49:51,780
We're miracle children!

675
00:50:09,965 --> 00:50:11,258
Go back.

676
00:50:12,759 --> 00:50:14,594
And don't let me ever see you again.

677
00:50:15,929 --> 00:50:17,431
I just want to live a quiet life.

678
00:50:28,984 --> 00:50:30,861
1999 HAESEONG
FREE LEGAL CONSULTATIONS

679
00:50:38,952 --> 00:50:40,537
Forget it. Stop thinking about it.

680
00:50:41,079 --> 00:50:42,873
It's got nothing to do with me.

681
00:50:43,749 --> 00:50:45,876
It's got nothing to do with me.

682
00:50:58,764 --> 00:51:01,058
I just came from Haeseong Hospital.

683
00:51:01,141 --> 00:51:03,935
Those cops have disappeared.

684
00:51:05,103 --> 00:51:08,106
We went through all that trouble
to save them, but they're gone.

685
00:51:08,607 --> 00:51:10,442
No record, and no one remembers them.

686
00:51:11,443 --> 00:51:12,486
What is this?

687
00:51:12,986 --> 00:51:15,614
You know what's going on, don't you?

688
00:51:16,198 --> 00:51:18,658
You're disrupting my work.
Could you please leave?

689
00:51:18,742 --> 00:51:20,118
Will that happen to us too?

690
00:51:22,037 --> 00:51:24,039
Could we disappear without a trace,

691
00:51:24,623 --> 00:51:26,374
just like those officers?

692
00:51:28,668 --> 00:51:29,836
Where would they take us?

693
00:51:31,046 --> 00:51:33,715
Would it be a government agency
like Mr. Nightmare said?

694
00:51:33,799 --> 00:51:37,135
What, are we going to be tortured
or actually vivisected?

695
00:51:38,095 --> 00:51:41,473
That's why you should stay quiet
and lie low, so you can't be found.

696
00:51:42,516 --> 00:51:44,434
Stop congregating and making it obvious.

697
00:51:55,320 --> 00:51:57,030
Let me ask you one thing.

698
00:51:58,240 --> 00:51:59,241
Does this power

699
00:52:00,408 --> 00:52:01,618
have an expiration date?

700
00:52:02,786 --> 00:52:07,791
I may not have died, but I did
come back from the brink of death.

701
00:52:07,874 --> 00:52:11,044
Ever since then,
my body's been strangely healthy.

702
00:52:13,171 --> 00:52:16,341
I don't run out of breath,
I don't bruise, and I don't get sick.

703
00:52:16,424 --> 00:52:18,426
Great, congratulations. Have a nice day.

704
00:52:21,680 --> 00:52:23,598
So I want to know what this power is.

705
00:52:23,682 --> 00:52:25,976
Exactly how I ended up with it

706
00:52:26,059 --> 00:52:27,352
and how to use it.

707
00:52:27,435 --> 00:52:31,481
It's not like I can go out and ask people.
They'd think I'd completely lost it.

708
00:52:32,649 --> 00:52:34,568
If I lose my powers,

709
00:52:35,986 --> 00:52:37,404
will I die again?

710
00:52:46,371 --> 00:52:47,873
You don't know Wunderkinder?

711
00:52:47,956 --> 00:52:50,500
Why do you keep bringing up
that Boon the King Duck?

712
00:52:52,460 --> 00:52:56,214
What is it? Is it a duck
whose genetics were successfully modified?

713
00:52:57,674 --> 00:52:59,134
I was so happy to be alive.

714
00:53:01,428 --> 00:53:02,512
Have I become a duck?

715
00:53:03,096 --> 00:53:04,598
No, it wasn't a success.

716
00:53:05,348 --> 00:53:06,349
It was a failure.

717
00:53:08,894 --> 00:53:09,811
An adverse effect.

718
00:53:11,229 --> 00:53:12,814
Mr. Lee Un-jeong.

719
00:53:18,069 --> 00:53:20,447
It's Kim Na-yeong
from the Welfare Department.

720
00:53:21,406 --> 00:53:22,866
Where are you?

721
00:53:23,575 --> 00:53:24,451
You should go.

722
00:53:24,534 --> 00:53:27,579
Not yet. What is
this "Boon the King Duck" thing?

723
00:53:27,662 --> 00:53:29,122
Am I a duck now or not?

724
00:53:29,206 --> 00:53:30,415
You're not, okay?

725
00:53:31,208 --> 00:53:33,960
I have nothing more to say,
so go ask someone else.

726
00:53:37,339 --> 00:53:40,258
Then should I go ask her instead?
What "Boon the King Duck" is?

727
00:53:41,259 --> 00:53:44,930
Should I ask her if she knows anything
since superpower guy here is clueless?

728
00:53:45,013 --> 00:53:47,766
- Un-jeong?
- What, you think I won't?

729
00:53:49,476 --> 00:53:50,310
This guy with su--

730
00:53:57,943 --> 00:54:00,111
You know I wouldn't be
the only one in trouble.

731
00:54:00,779 --> 00:54:01,780
Are you actually dumb?

732
00:54:02,364 --> 00:54:03,198
Dumb?

733
00:54:07,160 --> 00:54:09,204
- Let go of me.
- Quiet.

734
00:54:16,419 --> 00:54:17,796
Mr. Lee Un-jeong?

735
00:54:32,185 --> 00:54:34,062
Oh, there you are.

736
00:54:34,688 --> 00:54:38,566
It's just,
Mr. Yang asked me to help you out.

737
00:54:39,776 --> 00:54:42,028
I'm almost done, so I don't need any help.

738
00:54:45,657 --> 00:54:47,993
What happened to your face? How did that…

739
00:54:49,703 --> 00:54:50,537
I blush easily.

740
00:54:51,454 --> 00:54:53,164
Oh, you blush easily.

741
00:54:54,749 --> 00:54:57,377
The truth is, I came here
because I wanted to help you.

742
00:54:58,962 --> 00:55:02,966
You never come to any
of the staff dinners or get-togethers,

743
00:55:03,466 --> 00:55:06,428
and I've never had the chance
to talk to you alone.

744
00:55:06,511 --> 00:55:08,930
I was hoping you'd show up
to last week's dinner.

745
00:55:12,267 --> 00:55:15,312
Do we just need to line them up properly?

746
00:55:15,395 --> 00:55:16,479
Yes.

747
00:55:20,859 --> 00:55:21,985
That reminds me.

748
00:55:22,068 --> 00:55:24,738
You'll be at the street clean-up drive
this Friday, right?

749
00:55:24,821 --> 00:55:27,365
Have you put a team together yet?
If not, I could…

750
00:55:33,705 --> 00:55:37,208
I'll finish up here. I'll look forward to
seeing you at the street clean-up.

751
00:55:37,292 --> 00:55:38,543
Look forward to?

752
00:55:41,171 --> 00:55:44,007
Will you be joining the team dinner
after the clean-up?

753
00:55:44,090 --> 00:55:45,342
Of course. I'll be there.

754
00:55:46,301 --> 00:55:48,094
All right. See you then.

755
00:56:14,245 --> 00:56:17,332
Could you help me get down?

756
00:56:52,575 --> 00:56:55,245
Why would you hide something like this?

757
00:56:55,995 --> 00:56:56,830
Master!

758
00:57:09,717 --> 00:57:11,594
There's no expiration date.

759
00:57:13,346 --> 00:57:15,390
I almost died the first time too.

760
00:57:19,144 --> 00:57:20,061
Then…

761
00:57:28,403 --> 00:57:29,654
I ended up like this.

762
00:57:43,460 --> 00:57:44,627
You won't die.

763
00:58:09,027 --> 00:58:10,236
Hello!

764
00:58:10,320 --> 00:58:12,113
Hello to you all!

765
00:58:12,614 --> 00:58:15,575
I'm not dying anymore!

766
00:59:37,782 --> 00:59:38,992
Damn it.

767
01:00:03,349 --> 01:00:04,267
Hello?

768
01:00:05,018 --> 01:00:05,935
It's me.

769
01:00:06,019 --> 01:00:07,937
Master? What is it?

770
01:00:10,398 --> 01:00:11,232
Well…

771
01:00:14,861 --> 01:00:16,863
Are you free this Friday?

772
01:00:18,781 --> 01:00:20,658
I won't even ask why.

773
01:00:20,742 --> 01:00:23,453
I shall dedicate my Friday to you, Master.

774
01:00:24,996 --> 01:00:27,749
Yes, well, you don't have to go that far.

775
01:00:29,584 --> 01:00:31,210
Join me for the street clean-up.

776
01:00:34,589 --> 01:00:35,715
I need a team.

777
01:00:35,798 --> 01:00:38,885
Is that right?
Where are you right now, Master?

778
01:00:39,385 --> 01:00:42,305
Stay right where you are.
I'll zoom right over!

779
01:00:52,398 --> 01:00:53,483
Don't tell me…

780
01:00:55,360 --> 01:00:56,986
you just saved a defect.

781
01:01:05,161 --> 01:01:05,995
I did.

782
01:01:18,966 --> 01:01:20,468
Damn it.

783
01:01:21,844 --> 01:01:22,679
HAESEONG CITY HALL

784
01:01:22,762 --> 01:01:24,722
Is this my uniform?

785
01:01:26,057 --> 01:01:28,476
It's not as cool as I thought it would be.

786
01:01:29,227 --> 01:01:31,396
What do you think?
Do I look good in yellow?

787
01:01:31,479 --> 01:01:32,980
Blink once if I do.

788
01:01:37,485 --> 01:01:38,611
You shouldn't touch…

789
01:01:38,695 --> 01:01:39,570
Fascinating.

790
01:01:39,654 --> 01:01:41,197
Right, lunch.

791
01:01:41,280 --> 01:01:42,782
Lunch is important, isn't it?

792
01:01:42,865 --> 01:01:44,325
The food here is free, right?

793
01:01:44,409 --> 01:01:47,537
To think I'll be dining at City Hall!

794
01:01:48,079 --> 01:01:51,416
But I heard the food here sucks.
What food do you like, Master?

795
01:01:51,499 --> 01:01:52,917
Tell me everything you like.

796
01:01:53,000 --> 01:01:54,961
I won't make it for you, but Grandma will.

797
01:01:56,546 --> 01:01:59,382
I'm the granddaughter of Hearty House,

798
01:01:59,465 --> 01:02:01,926
Eun Chae-ni!

799
01:02:03,803 --> 01:02:06,889
Hey, there's a massage stick here!

800
01:02:06,973 --> 01:02:08,891
I'm sure you all have stiff shoulders.

801
01:02:08,975 --> 01:02:09,976
Is this your desk?

802
01:02:27,535 --> 01:02:29,287
Eunie, where the heck are you?

803
01:02:30,329 --> 01:02:32,957
Ignoring my calls all day!
Are you itching for a fight?

804
01:02:33,541 --> 01:02:35,376
I've been busy. Sorry.

805
01:02:35,460 --> 01:02:37,128
It's nothing major,

806
01:02:37,795 --> 01:02:39,839
but I landed a job at City Hall.

807
01:02:41,215 --> 01:02:42,425
What nonsense is that?

808
01:02:42,508 --> 01:02:43,885
Hold on a second.

809
01:02:43,968 --> 01:02:44,886
Master, come here.

810
01:02:44,969 --> 01:02:48,055
- Get over here. It's urgent.
- Who's she calling Master?

811
01:02:48,139 --> 01:02:50,224
Tell my grandma that I got a job.

812
01:02:50,308 --> 01:02:51,142
- But--
- Hurry.

813
01:02:51,225 --> 01:02:53,394
A job! Tell her I got a job.

814
01:02:53,895 --> 01:02:55,480
Yes, hello.

815
01:02:55,563 --> 01:02:58,065
I'm Lee Un-jeong
of the Civil Complaints Office

816
01:02:58,149 --> 01:02:59,400
at Haeseong City Hall.

817
01:03:00,067 --> 01:03:00,985
Why, of course!

818
01:03:01,486 --> 01:03:03,571
You have my full blessing!

819
01:03:03,654 --> 01:03:04,530
Pardon? Oh, I…

820
01:03:05,031 --> 01:03:06,407
That's not it.

821
01:03:06,491 --> 01:03:10,244
Although it's a temporary position,
Ms. Eun Chae-ni did get a job here.

822
01:03:10,328 --> 01:03:11,329
I'm just confirming…

823
01:03:12,038 --> 01:03:14,624
- Tell her more.
- So, my Chae-ni really…

824
01:03:14,707 --> 01:03:17,710
- That's all you have to say?
- She really found a job at City Hall?

825
01:03:17,794 --> 01:03:19,670
What more should I say? You talk to her.

826
01:03:19,754 --> 01:03:23,466
Grandma, I'm officially on duty,
so I'm really busy. I'll call you later.

827
01:03:23,549 --> 01:03:24,967
My Eunie is really

828
01:03:25,468 --> 01:03:27,428
on the government's payroll?

829
01:03:35,478 --> 01:03:36,312
Hello.

830
01:03:37,605 --> 01:03:38,439
Hello.

831
01:03:38,940 --> 01:03:39,899
Hello…

832
01:03:40,399 --> 01:03:42,360
Hello there. Hello.

833
01:03:42,443 --> 01:03:45,196
No wonder Eunie's fortune
mentioned a government career!

834
01:03:45,279 --> 01:03:47,281
Why, hello there. Hello to you too.

835
01:03:47,365 --> 01:03:49,200
Hello! And hello to you too!

836
01:03:49,283 --> 01:03:52,870
My granddaughter got a job!

837
01:03:52,954 --> 01:03:54,747
Hello. Hello there!

838
01:03:54,831 --> 01:03:56,916
Goodness me!

839
01:03:56,999 --> 01:03:58,876
Why, hello there!

840
01:03:58,960 --> 01:04:00,711
Hello! Hello to you all!

841
01:04:01,212 --> 01:04:03,548
I'm telling you, she got a job!

842
01:04:03,631 --> 01:04:07,093
HEARTY HOUSE

843
01:04:07,176 --> 01:04:09,637
Guys! Ha-na, Du-na, Won-ju, Sang-ju!

844
01:04:09,720 --> 01:04:12,598
Put the rice cake pot on the stove.
It's a family celebration!

845
01:04:13,099 --> 01:04:16,602
Our Chae-ni is going to work
for the government!

846
01:04:20,064 --> 01:04:22,692
Why are you all just standing there?

847
01:04:22,775 --> 01:04:25,111
Go soak the rice, okay?

848
01:04:25,194 --> 01:04:27,780
You have guests.

849
01:04:49,176 --> 01:04:50,720
You haven't changed one bit,

850
01:04:51,220 --> 01:04:52,054
Madam King.

851
01:04:53,890 --> 01:04:55,600
Won-ju, close the store.

852
01:08:29,980 --> 01:08:34,985
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi
